{
  "_notes": [
    "Reference template for universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py using the renamed Nabataea PNG pack.",
    "Extract Nabatea_renamed_for_pipeline.zip into C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/. The ZIP contains a Nabatea folder, so the final PNG paths should be C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/Nabatea/*.png.",
    "mod_data_dir is intentionally omitted so check/build can run before the mod folder exists. Use --mod-data-dir in PowerShell when importing into an installed mod.",
    "PowerShell check: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\Nabataea_art_reference_v1.json --check-only",
    "PowerShell build: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\Nabataea_art_reference_v1.json",
    "Normal and alpha icons use the Spartan League v8 footprint: 0.65625 of each cell, so 256px cells get about 168px visible art.",
    "Unit flags are kept on the separate Civ V unit-flag profile, not the normal circular-icon footprint.",
    "Normal atlas index map: 0 civ, 1 leader, 2 CamelSkirmisher, 3 DesertProwler, 4 DesertCistern, 5 RockCutTreasury, 6 IncenseRouteTrait, 7 SandstormAmbush.",
    "Black-background glyph sources retain their _black filename suffix and are processed through black-to-transparent glyph profiles.",
    "SOURCE_RENAME_MAP.md is included for provenance of the corrected filenames. It is not consumed by the pipeline."
  ],
